Background

		Mr. Stephen R. Hardis served as an Executive Advisor and Member of Advisory Board at Aquiline Capital Partners LLC. Mr. Hardis served as the Chief Executive Officer of Eaton Corporation. Mr. Hardis served as an Executive Vice President of Finance and Administration of Eaton's since 1979 and Vice Chairman and Chief Financial and Administrative Officer since 1986 where he joined in 1979. He served as Eaton's Chairman from January 1996 to July 31, 2000 and Eaton's Vice ... Chairman since 1986. He served in executive roles during his more than 20 years at the firmMr. Hardis is a Director of Apogent Technologies Inc. Mr. Hardis served as Independent Director of Lexmark International, Inc. from November 1996 to November 29, 2016. He is also a Director of Parkwood Corporation. He is an emeritus trustee of The Cleveland Clinic. He serves as a Director of the Cleveland Clinic Foundation (hospital).He serves as a Trustee of The Musical Arts Association (Cleveland Orchestra) and Cleveland Clinic. He has been a Director of Marsh & Mclennan Companies Inc., since 1998. He is the former chairman of the board of Marsh & McLennan Companies, Inc. since May 2006. He has been a Director of American Greetings Corp. since 1999. He served as an Independent Director of Progressive Corp. from 1988 to May 13, 2016 and served as its Lead Independent Director from November 2013 to May 13, 2016. He served as a Director of Axcelis Technologies Inc. since 2000 and as its Lead Director since May 2005 until May 13, 2015. Mr. Hardis served as the Chairman of the Board of Axcelis Technologies, Inc., from May 2000 to May 2006. He served as Director of Steris Corp. since September 2000.Read Full Background




