News




Our Company
News
News Releases











 




 



CLEVELAND, OH...Eaton Corporation's Board of Directors today elected Stephen R. Hardis the company's ninth Chairman of the Board, effective January 1, 1996. Hardis, 60, succeeds William E. Butler, who had previously indicated his intent to retire at the end of 1995. Butler is 64. 
At the company's annual meeting on April 26th, Hardis was named Chief Executive Officer, effective September 1, 1995, and the board indicated at that time that he would succeed Butler as board chairman. 
Hardis began his career with Eaton in 1979 as Executive Vice President-Finance and Administration. He was elected to the board of directors in 1983, and in 1986 became Vice Chairman and Chief Financial and Administrative Officer. 
Eaton Corporation is a global manufacturer of highly engineered products which serve vehicle, industrial, construction, commercial and aerospace markets. Principal products include truck transmissions and axles, engine components, hydraulic products, electrical power distribution and control equipment, ion implanters and a wide variety of controls. Headquartered in Cleveland, the company has 52,000 employees and 150 manufacturing sites in 22 countries around the world. Sales for 1994 were $6.1 billion. 



 



 



